				<name type="primary" sortindex="5" value="The Pie Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Welcome to the The Pie Game card game! Grandma needs your help, she signed up for the local bake sale to make one of her award-winning pies, but her bursitis is acting up and this is preventing her from making her pie. Can you help Grandma make the pie and save the day or will you disgrace Grandma by not getting your pie made?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For 2 to 8 players ages 6 and up. Game setup is simple as each player is dealt 1 of 8 unique recipe cards, such as: Apple Pie, Chocolate Cream Pie, Key Lime and others. Each recipe card lists the 5 ingredients that you need for your pie recipe. Next, each player is dealt 5 ingredient cards. The ingredients are all fresh and delicious with favorites like: Whipped Cream, Lime Juice, Chocolate Cookie Crust, Brown Sugar and Milk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Play is just as easy, each player attempts to collect all recipe ingredients for their Pie as game play progresses through card draw and discard. Players draw new ingredient cards from the pile and discard unwanted ingredient cards from their hand to maintain 5 ingredient cards at all times. But watch out, because three could be trouble at every turn with Fudge and Double Fudge cards with the likes of: &amp;ldquo;Your neighbor wants to borrow some eggs&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;The cat knocked the sugar bowl off the counter&amp;rdquo;, these can cause you to discard, trade or pass your pie ingredient cards or even, lose a turn!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to collect all 5 ingredients needed for their Pie recipe wins that round. Once someone completes their Pie, all recipe and ingredient cards are collected and redealt and the first person to win 3 rounds (or as many, or few rounds as everyone wants to play) wins the game&amp;hellip; all other players have to disappoint Grandma and tell her they did not get their pie done (or maybe they just lose). So, don&amp;rsquo;t let Grandma down!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
